MongoDB is backend DB stroing a non sql type 
In localHost DB is hosted on the 27017 port.
usually in the app.js file DB is installed <>> npm i mongoose>,, 
>>constant mongoose=require ("mongoose")
>>mongoose.connect("mongodb://locolhost:27017//todolistDB", {useNewUrlParser: true });

Mongoose Schema - 
const <schemName>{     (const itemName+{})
  <fieldName>: <FiledDataType>,   (ex ; name : string)
}


Mongoose DB Model 
const = ,ongoose.model (
<"SingularCollectionName">,
<schemaName>
)

Ex - const Item = mongoose.model("Item", itemSchema(from above));



For more related to mongoose ,, check on the Mogoosejs.com,,
you will get many mongoose schema, model etc,, yo can directly pick from there ,, and use it 
